ZH: 他们一直在捕风捉影地寻找失踪的孩子。
EN: They have been chasing shadows in search of the missing child.

ZH: 我们不能只凭直觉，而需要有确凿的证据，不能一直捕风捉影。
EN: We can't just rely on intuition, we need solid evidence, can't always chase shadows.

ZH: 他们的指控只是捕风捉影，没有任何事实根据。
EN: Their accusations are just catching shadows, without any factual basis.

ZH: 我们不能轻信陌生人的谣言，免得捕风捉影。
EN: We can't easily believe rumors from strangers, to avoid chasing shadows.

ZH: 他经常因为捕风捉影而惹上麻烦。
EN: He often gets into trouble because of chasing shadows.

ZH: 这种行为很像捕风捉影，毫无意义。
EN: This behavior is like catching shadows, meaningless.

ZH: 他的猜疑很大程度上是捕风捉影的结果。
EN: His suspicions are largely the result of chasing shadows.

ZH: 如果你经常捕风捉影，就不容易明辨是非。
EN: If you often chase shadows, it is not easy to distinguish right from wrong.

ZH: 她把别人的意图误解为对她的威胁，简直是在捕风捉影。
EN: She misinterprets others' intentions as threats to her, it's simply chasing shadows.

ZH: 我们不应该在没有确凿证据的情况下随便捕风捉影。
EN: We shouldn't chase shadows without solid evidence.

ZH: 他一直在捕风捉影地猜测她的真实意图。
EN: He has been speculating on her true intentions by chasing shadows.

ZH: 这个谣言显然是捕风捉影的结果。
EN: This rumor is obviously the result of chasing shadows.

ZH: 我们不能被无关的事物所干扰，免得捕风捉影。
EN: We can't be distracted by irrelevant things, to avoid chasing shadows.

ZH: 如果相信谣言，只会让自己一直捕风捉影。
EN: Believing in rumors will only make oneself chase shadows.

ZH: 他不能因为一时的情绪而捕风捉影。
EN: He can't chase shadows because of temporary emotions.

ZH: 不要因为别人的挑拨而捕风捉影。
EN: Don't chase shadows because of someone else's provocation.

ZH: 她总是捕风捉影地怀疑他人的动机。
EN: She always suspects others' motives by chasing shadows.

ZH: 即使不确定的事情也不能轻易捕风捉影。
EN: Even uncertain things should not be easily chased.

ZH: 他的忧虑是由于捕风捉影造成的。
EN: His worries are caused by chasing shadows.

ZH: 记者应该有责任避免捕风捉影。
EN: Journalists should have the responsibility to avoid chasing shadows.
